    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1972-10-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1972-10-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="64"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                <head>64. National Security Decision Memorandum 192 <lb/> Council for International
                    Economic Policy Decision Memorandum 15<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d64fn1"
                        >Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM_1">Nixon</persName>
                        Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Box H–208,
                            <gloss target="#t_NSDM_1">NSDM</gloss> 151–<gloss target="#t_NSDM_1"
                            >NSDM</gloss> 200, Originals. Secret; <gloss target="#t_NODIS_1"
                            >Nodis</gloss>. Copies were sent to the Secretaries of Commerce and
                        Treasury.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1972-10-18">October 18, 1972</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Lend-Lease Negotiations with the <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <head>REFERENCE</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_NSDM_1">NSDM</gloss> 190/<gloss target="#t_CIEPDM_1"
                            >CIEPDM</gloss> 12<note n="2" xml:id="d64fn2">
                            <ref target="#d49">Document 49</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has made the following decisions:</p>
                <p>1. The “total Soviet obligation to the United States” referred to in paragraph 1
                    of the <gloss target="#t_NSDM_1">NSDM</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_CIEPDM_1"
                        >CIEPDM</gloss> under reference shall be set at $722 million.</p>
                <p>2. The US negotiators are authorized to reduce the interest rate on deferred
                    installments referred to in paragraph 4 of the <gloss target="#t_NSDM_1"
                        >NSDM</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_CIEPDM_1">CIEPDM</gloss> under reference to
                        3%.<note n="3" xml:id="d64fn3">In message <gloss target="#t_TOHAK_1"
                            >Tohak</gloss> 36 to <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>,
                        who was in Paris for the peace negotiations, October 18, <persName
                            corresp="#p_HAM_1">Haig</persName> wrote: “As a result of a call from me
                        to <persName corresp="#p_DAF_1">Dobrynin</persName> last night and a last
                        minute crunch session among <persName corresp="#p_PPG_1"
                        >Peterson</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SH_3">Sonnenfeldt</persName> and
                            <persName corresp="#p_PTS_1">Patolichev</persName> at <persName
                            corresp="#p_PPG_1">Peterson</persName>’s house last night, the
                        lend-lease package was settled at a surface formula of 722/3. While this was
                        our rock bottom position, Pete is confident that he can handle it on the
                        Hill and I believe the Soviets are returning home with the feeling that they
                        redressed the problems resulting from the maritime agreement.” (National
                        Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM_1">Nixon</persName> Presidential
                        Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, <persName
                            corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName> Office Files, Box 25, <gloss
                            target="#t_HAK_1">HAK</gloss> Paris/Saigon Trip, TOHAK, October 16–23,
                        1972)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_KHA_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                        <note n="4" xml:id="d64fn4">
                            <persName corresp="#p_HAM_1">Haig</persName> signed for <persName
                                corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName> above <persName
                                corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>’s typed signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                    <signed corresp="#p_FP_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_FP_1">Peter Flanigan</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
